  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is called <html:em><html:strong>inhabited</html:strong></html:em> when we have an element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {toProp}\,A]]></fr:tex>. When we say <html:em><html:strong>there exists</html:strong></html:em>, we refer to inhabitation.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
